   useEffect(() => {
     if (!author.length & !quote.length) {
       waitForTask(fetchData());
     }
   });
 }



 You might run into a scary â€œmemory access out of boundsâ€Â error. Itâ€™sÂ quite common to see in plugin and widget development. Just restart Figma and it wonâ€™t be there anymore.



 You might have noticed that sometimes, the quote text contains weird characters.







 These areÂ Unicode charactersÂ and we must properly format them in code:



 <!-- ui.html -->
 <script>
