 So far, so good â€” both rows take up the entire width. We can use that as our base layout for small screens.







 But maybe we want to introduce the narrower text when the viewport reaches a larger width. We can use what we know about the full-stop character to â€œskipâ€ columns. Letâ€™s have the text ident skip the first and last columns in this case.



