Weâ€™re looking at loaders in this series. More than that, weâ€™re breaking down some common loader patterns and how to re-create them with nothing more than a single div. So far, weâ€™ve picked apart the classic spinning loader. Now, letâ€™s look at another one youâ€™re likely well aware of: the dots.



 Dot loaders are all over the place. Theyâ€™re neat because they usually consist of three dots that sort of look like a text ellipsis (â€¦) that dances around.








